Class KillJob

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ow2.proactive.scheduler.common.task.executable.JavaExecutable
      • org.ow2.proactive.scheduler.examples.KillJob

  • public class KillJob
extends JavaExecutable
    KillJob is a task that will kill the JVM 5 seconds after start. Used only by Test classes.

        public Serializable execute(TaskResult... results)
                     throws Throwable
        Description copied from class: JavaExecutable
        The content of this method will be executed once after being scheduled.
        This may generate a result as an Object. It can be whatever you want.
        The results list order correspond to the order in the dependence list.
        Specified by:
        execute in class JavaExecutable
        Parameters:
        results - the results (as a taskResult) from parent tasks.
        Returns:
        any serializable object from the user.
        Throws:
        Throwable - any exception thrown by the user's code
        See Also:
        JavaExecutable.execute(TaskResult[])
